HEADWORD: Turbary
<hw>Tur"ba*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Turbaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. <ets>turbaria</ets> a
place for digging peat, from <ets>turba</ets> peat. See
<er>Turf</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A right of digging turf
on another man's land; also, the ground where turf is dug.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

